---
/**
 * consensus-deep-dive · Figure 6 — the consensus protocol family tree
 * (Paxos → Multi-Paxos → Raft / EPaxos).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/distributed-systems/consensus-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Isolated as an .astro component because MDX's JSX
 * parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes. It
 * references marker-end="url(#arw)" (fill #6b675f), declared once in the source's
 * top-of-body <svg defs> and inlined here in a local <defs> so the figure
 * resolves standalone.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Family tree of consensus protocols: single-decree Paxos, Multi-Paxos, Raft, and EPaxos leaderless, all crash-fault-tolerant"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect
                x="200"
                y="14"
                width="200"
                height="40"
                rx="9"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="300"
                y="32"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">Paxos (single-decree)</text
            >
            <text x="300" y="47" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >prepare/promise → accept/accepted · minimal, hard</text
            >
            <line x1="300" y1="54" x2="300" y2="78" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <rect x="200" y="80" width="200" height="40" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text
                x="300"
                y="98"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">Multi-Paxos</text
            >
            <text x="300" y="113" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >stable leader runs a log · what most "Paxos" means</text
            >
            <line x1="245" y1="120" x2="160" y2="150" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
            ></line>
            <line x1="355" y1="120" x2="440" y2="150" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
            ></line>
            <rect x="40" y="152" width="240" height="42" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="160"
                y="170"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">Raft</text
            >
            <text x="160" y="185" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >strong leader · easy to implement · leader = throughput ceiling</text
            >
            <rect x="320" y="152" width="240" height="42" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#8a5a00"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="440"
                y="170"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#8a5a00">EPaxos / leaderless</text
            >
            <text x="440" y="185" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >commuting cmds need no order · low latency · complex</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        All provide the same safety. Raft &amp; Multi-Paxos are <strong
            >crash-fault-tolerant (CFT)</strong
        >: they assume nodes fail by <em>stopping</em>, not by lying — which is the last, biggest
        step.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
